## Working Rules (reminder)

- Every module has a MODULE_CONTRACT (PCAM: Purpose, Constraints, Autonomy, Metrics).
- Every code change either updates the knowledge graph or is a private-helper edit inside an already-governed file.
- Every bug fix adds a regression entry to `docs/verification-plan.xml`.
- Every new external dependency is justified in `development-plan.xml` (size, maintenance, license).
- Log markers use the `[Module][function][BLOCK_NAME]` convention.
- XML artifacts use **unique ID-based tags** (`<M-CONFIG>`, not `<Module ID="M-CONFIG">`).

## Escape Hatch

If a specific task genuinely does not need GRACE (e.g. a pure typo fix in a comment), say so
explicitly in your first message ("using GRACE-bypass for trivial typo") so the log is honest.
Do NOT silently skip activation.

